1. Linux redis4 5.4.78-2-pve #1 SMP PVE 5.4.78-2 (Thu, 03 Dec 2020 14:26:17 +0100) x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux
2. Ubuntu 20.04 as lxc container
2. I enabled appendonly persistence

comments_data.body: Looks like it gave us a nice concise error message, `3842:S 18 Feb 2021 22:14:27.831 # RDB has duplicated key '' in DB 0` so there is some corruption in your rdb file where you have duplicate empty keys. Do you have any idea how that could have happened?

The interesting thing is that after that error he started anew automatically and it went through!
I hd the same issue on 3 of 7 nodes of the same redis cluster as I turned off rbd save and enabled appendonly. I did not had the issue before and the also on the other 4 hosts it was not an issue with the same dataset

Had almost the same error...
I upgraded from PVE6 to PVE7 (maybe this is important).
